{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17564257","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17564257"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T23:11:34+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T23:11:34+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16951"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"16951","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/16951"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.03,0.53,0.42,0.01,0.01]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9641"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"109506"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"9641","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/9641"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16951"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"91878"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"11"},{"type":"tags","id":"14"},{"type":"tags","id":"27"},{"type":"tags","id":"65"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"108"},{"type":"tags","id":"1061"},{"type":"tags","id":"2267"},{"type":"tags","id":"2436"},{"type":"tags","id":"2701"},{"type":"tags","id":"4174"},{"type":"tags","id":"4976"},{"type":"tags","id":"4982"},{"type":"tags","id":"8118"},{"type":"tags","id":"8989"},{"type":"tags","id":"11625"},{"type":"tags","id":"11635"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"22740"},{"type":"contributions","id":"30624"},{"type":"contributions","id":"36530"},{"type":"contributions","id":"36532"},{"type":"contributions","id":"43674"},{"type":"contributions","id":"44436"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"109506","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/109506"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 52-year-old man presents to the General Practice clinic with three months of worsening shortness of breath, productive cough, and fatigue. He has also experienced a five kilogram weight loss over the past four months and intermittent chills. He has worked as a sandblaster for 25 years and was diagnosed with silicosis eight years ago. He has no other significant medical history and takes no regular medications. He lives in a boarding house with shared facilities and is a current smoker with a 30 pack-year history.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOn examination, he appears unwell. His pulse rate is 95/min, blood pressure 128/78 mmHg, respiratory rate 24/min, SpO2 92% on room air, and temperature 37.8\u00b0C. There are coarse crackles throughout both lung fields. His chest X-ray shows progression of upper lobe opacities compared to imaging from six months ago.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most urgent investigation?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Spirometry","High-resolution chest CT scan","Sputum acid-fast bacilli testing","Antinuclear antibody testing","Alpha-1 antitrypsin level"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":[],"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis patient presents with features highly concerning for silicotuberculosis - the combination of silicosis and active tuberculosis. The worsening respiratory symptoms, weight loss, chills, low-grade fever, and progression of radiological changes in a patient with established silicosis should raise immediate suspicion for tuberculosis as a complication. His living situation in shared facilities increases his risk of tuberculosis exposure and transmission.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESputum acid-fast bacilli testing\u003C/strong\u003E is the most urgent investigation as it can directly identify mycobacterial infection. Silica exposure impairs macrophage function and increases the risk of tuberculosis by up to 30-fold. Early diagnosis and treatment of tuberculosis is crucial both for the patient\u0027s health and for public health infection control measures.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EHigh-resolution chest CT scan\u003C/strong\u003E might provide detailed imaging of the lung parenchyma but would delay the critical diagnosis of tuberculosis. More importantly, there are significant safety and public health concerns about missing tuberculosis - the patient could continue to transmit infection to others in his boarding house and healthcare settings. CT scanning should not take priority over urgent microbiological diagnosis when tuberculosis is strongly suspected.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESpirometry\u003C/strong\u003E would document the degree of airflow limitation but would not help diagnose the cause of the acute deterioration. It may also pose an infection risk to staff and other patients if tuberculosis is present, and should be deferred until tuberculosis is excluded.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAntinuclear antibody testing\u003C/strong\u003E would be appropriate if an autoimmune condition was suspected, but the clinical presentation and occupational history make tuberculosis far more likely and urgent to exclude.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAlpha-1 antitrypsin level\u003C/strong\u003E would be relevant for investigating emphysema in a younger patient or those with a family history, but would not address the acute deterioration or the high suspicion of tuberculosis in this clinical context.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Silicosis increases the risk of tuberculosis infection by up to 30-fold due to impaired macrophage function.","Silicotuberculosis typically presents with worsening respiratory symptoms in a patient with known silicosis.","Urgent tuberculosis testing is essential when tuberculosis is suspected due to public health and infection control implications."],"references":["Lanzafame M, Vento S. Mini-review: Silico-tuberculosis. Journal of Clinical Tuberculosis and Other Mycobacterial Diseases. 2021 May 1. Available at: https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S2405579421000073","Cowie RL. The epidemiology of tuberculosis in gold miners with silicosis. Am J Respir Crit Care Med. 1994;150(5):1460\u20131462. Available at: https://doi.org/10.1164/ajrccm.150.5.7952562","World Health Organization (WHO). Tuberculosis and Silicosis. 2023. Available at: https://www.who.int"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"91878"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16951"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"91878","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/91878"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-07-22T02:34:55+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-07-22T03:03:00+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9641"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"109506"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"11","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/11"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\udec1","name":"Respiratory Medicine","synonyms":["Pulmonology"],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"14","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/14"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\udda0","name":"Infectious Diseases","synonyms":["ID"],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2021-05-21T07:51:58+09:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"27","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/27"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udc77","name":"Occupational/Environmental Medicine","synonym